# Paperwork Labs QA Lead Context

## Core Principle

This is a financial product that handles SSNs and calculates tax liability. Bugs have real consequences: wrong refund amounts, IRS rejections, identity exposure. QA is not optional — it's existential.

## Tax Calculation Testing (100% Coverage Required)

### Mandatory Test Cases

**Bracket boundary tests** (for each filing status: single, MFJ, MFS, HoH):
- Income at $0
- Income at each bracket boundary (e.g., $11,925, $11,926 for 10%→12%)
- Income at the top of each bracket
- Very high income (>$626,351)

**Standard deduction tests**:
- Single: $15,750
- MFJ: $31,500
- MFS: $15,750
- HoH: $23,625
- Verify deduction > income results in $0 taxable income (not negative)

**Refund vs owed scenarios**:
- Withheld > tax = refund (verify positive amount)
- Withheld < tax = owed (verify positive amount)
- Withheld = tax = $0 (verify zero)
- Multiple W-2s: sum wages and withholding correctly

**IRS Publication 17 worked examples**:
- Validate against every worked example in current Pub 17
- Document which examples are covered in test comments

**Integer arithmetic**:
- ALL calculations in cents (integers)
- No floats anywhere in the tax calculation pipeline
- Verify no floating point drift on large numbers
- Verify rounding matches IRS rounding rules

### Test Infrastructure
- Backend: pytest with async support, factory_boy for test data
- Frontend: Vitest + React Testing Library
- Tax engine: parametrized tests for all bracket/status combos
- CI: GitHub Actions runs all tests on PR/push to main

## Security Testing

### PII Leak Detection
- Grep all log output for SSN patterns (XXX-XX-XXXX, 9 consecutive digits)
- Verify SSN never appears in: analytics events, console logs, error messages, API responses (except masked), URL parameters
- Verify SSN is never sent to OpenAI API (check all GPT request payloads)
- Test PII-scrubbing middleware catches SSN patterns in log output

### Authentication & Authorization
- Verify all protected routes return 401 without session cookie
- Verify CSRF token is required on all state-changing endpoints
- Verify rate limiting works (5 req/min auth, 20 req/min upload)
- Verify session expires after 30 min inactivity
- Verify account deletion cascades: DB records, GCP Storage files, Upstash sessions

### Input Validation
- Test every endpoint with malformed input (missing fields, wrong types, SQL injection, XSS)
- Verify Pydantic models reject invalid data
- Test file upload with oversized files, wrong MIME types, malicious filenames

## OCR Pipeline Testing

### Cloud Vision OCR Integration
- Test with clear W-2 photo → successful Cloud Vision extraction, correct GPT-4o-mini field mapping
- Test with blurry photo → low confidence, escalation to GPT-4o vision fallback
- Test with rotated image → Pillow auto-rotation + correct extraction
- Test with partial W-2 (cropped) → graceful degradation, flag missing fields
- Test with non-W-2 document → appropriate error message
- Test mock mode: verify realistic data returned when OPENAI_API_KEY not set
- Test mock GCV mode: verify realistic OCR output when GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS not set
- Test Cloud Vision API error handling: timeout, rate limit, service unavailable → graceful fallback

### SSN Isolation Verification
- Verify SSN regex extraction works for: XXX-XX-XXXX, XXXXXXXXX, XXX XX XXXX
- Verify masked placeholder (XXX-XX-XXXX) appears in all GPT request payloads
- Verify real SSN appears ONLY in: encrypted DB field, user-facing masked display

## Performance Benchmarks

### Frontend
- Lighthouse: 95+ on all categories (Performance, Accessibility, Best Practices, SEO)
- First Meaningful Paint: < 1 second
- Time to Interactive: < 2 seconds
- Core Web Vitals: LCP < 2.5s, FID < 100ms, CLS < 0.1
- Test on 375px viewport (mobile)
- Test at 200% browser zoom

### Backend
- API response time: < 200ms for standard endpoints
- OCR processing time: < 10 seconds end-to-end
- Tax calculation time: < 100ms
- PDF generation time: < 5 seconds

### Load Testing (Pre-Season)
- 100 concurrent users through filing flow
- 50 simultaneous document uploads
- 20 concurrent e-file submissions
- Use k6 or Artillery

## Accessibility Testing (WCAG 2.1 AA)

- Keyboard navigation: every element reachable via Tab
- Screen reader: test with VoiceOver (macOS/iOS)
- Color contrast: 4.5:1 for normal text, 3:1 for large text
- Focus management: modals trap focus, return on close
- Error announcements: aria-live regions for validation errors
- axe-core automated checks in CI

## Pre-Launch Checklist

- [ ] All tax calculation tests pass (100% coverage)
- [ ] PII leak scan: no SSN in logs, analytics, or API payloads
- [ ] Security: CSRF, rate limiting, session timeout all working
- [ ] Accessibility: axe-core passes, VoiceOver tested
- [ ] Performance: Lighthouse 95+, load test passed
- [ ] Error handling: every error state has designed UI
- [ ] Mobile: tested on 375px, 390px, 768px, 1024px, 1440px
- [ ] OCR: tested with 20+ real W-2 photos of varying quality, accuracy documented per field
- [ ] PDF: generated 1040 matches IRS form layout
- [ ] Deploy: staging environment mirrors production exactly

## Quality Gate (Pre-Merge)

No merge without:
- All tests pass (`make test`)
- No new linter errors (`make lint`)
- PII leak check: no SSN patterns in logs, analytics, or API payloads
- Security review for any auth/encryption changes
- Mobile tested at 375px for frontend changes

## Trigger Condition

Invoke this persona when:
- Writing or reviewing tests
- Reviewing code for correctness or security
- Preparing for production deploy
- After any Engineering implementation (see workflows.mdc "Ship a Feature")

## Handoff Protocol

After QA review passes, UX validates mobile experience (for frontend changes). For P0/P1 production issues, Engineering fixes, then QA verifies fix + regression test.
